It's been used since
the turn of the century,

44:41.946 --> 44:45.615
But dr. Jack lippes
recently refined it

44:45.617 --> 44:48.418
Using something
called thermoplastics,

44:48.420 --> 44:50.086
Making it the
most effective

44:50.088 --> 44:54.257
And simple method
of birth control
available today.

44:54.259 --> 44:56.359
Birth control?

44:56.660 --> 44:57.694
My mother
would never allow that.

44:57.696 --> 45:00.196
You're 18
and don't need your
mother's permission.

45:00.198 --> 45:02.699
As your doctor,
I am telling you,

45:02.701 --> 45:05.802
This is the first step...

45:05.936 --> 45:08.371
In solving your problem.

45:12.543 --> 45:16.012
Some little thing
made out of plastic?

45:16.014 --> 45:19.649
How is that
supposed to stop me
from acting like a whore?

45:19.651 --> 45:21.150
Don't...

45:21.152 --> 45:24.087
Don't say that
ever again, rose.

45:25.656 --> 45:27.623
There is...

45:28.058 --> 45:31.694
Such promise
of hope ahead.

45:31.696 --> 45:35.798
You are not gonna
have to suffer
like this forever.

45:35.800 --> 45:40.636
But while we
wait for the answers
that will surely come,

45:40.871 --> 45:44.874
The least we can do
is make sure you don't
get pregnant again.

45:44.876 --> 45:47.076
(baby wailing)

45:47.678 --> 45:50.279
Hunger, gas.

45:50.481 --> 45:51.981
You're not wet.

45:51.983 --> 45:54.650
What are the other
reasons a baby cries?

45:54.652 --> 45:56.686
Babies like
a tight swaddle.

45:56.688 --> 45:59.222
I'm gonna heat
another bottle.

45:59.224 --> 46:01.758
(wailing continues)

46:09.566 --> 46:10.466
You're home late.

46:10.468 --> 46:12.835
Did something go wrong
at the new job?

46:12.837 --> 46:15.371
The new job is fine.

46:15.373 --> 46:17.573
Seems home
is a different story.

46:17.575 --> 46:18.908
He's only crying
because he's hungry.

46:18.910 --> 46:20.576
I was about
to heat a bottle.

46:20.578 --> 46:22.945
(wailing continues)

46:24.715 --> 46:26.949
(wailing stops)

46:29.987 --> 46:32.088
(sighs)

46:34.424 --> 46:37.760
Swaddle needed
to be tighter is all.

46:38.262 --> 46:41.330
I think I might have
mentioned his swaddle.

46:41.332 --> 46:42.665
And I been
telling miss libby

46:42.667 --> 46:44.200
About my auntie's
swaddle all day.

46:44.202 --> 46:48.671
(chuckles)
my auntie was the
queen of the swaddles.

46:52.276 --> 46:54.911
Long may she reign.

46:57.681 --> 47:00.783
Maybe you were
right about the girl.

47:01.151 --> 47:03.820
She does seem...

47:04.788 --> 47:06.856
Competent.

47:16.934 --> 47:19.202
Um, I need to talk
to you about something.

47:19.204 --> 47:21.938
About rose, that girl
with the witch of a mother,

47:21.940 --> 47:22.905
Trying to yank
out her uterus.

47:22.907 --> 47:25.241
Have you been looking
through my patient files?

47:25.243 --> 47:29.245
The way you
were yelling, people in
space know about rose.

47:29.247 --> 47:32.515
My point is, I know
these kind of situations,

47:32.517 --> 47:36.319
And you need to talk to her,
have a real heart-to-heart...

47:36.321 --> 47:40.056
I will not discuss
my patients with you ever.

47:40.058 --> 47:42.058
Is that clear?

47:42.459 --> 47:43.960
'cause you
know everything!

47:43.962 --> 47:45.494
Ooh! I'm sorry.

47:45.496 --> 47:46.028
Can I help?

47:46.030 --> 47:50.633
Oh, my god.
$50 shoe, and it breaks
just like the $5 kind.

47:50.635 --> 47:53.903
You're making
house calls now?

47:53.905 --> 47:55.204
Thanks for your concern.

47:55.206 --> 47:56.672
You don't remember me,
do you?

47:56.674 --> 47:59.642
Enjoy your day!
Nice to see you again.

48:02.913 --> 48:04.013
Who was that?

48:04.015 --> 48:06.916
Nobody.
Good samaritan.

48:06.918 --> 48:08.985
(elevator bell dings)

48:25.569 --> 48:27.536
(door closes)

48:51.461 --> 48:56.632
<i>Positively the...</i>
<i>The original hellfire</i>
<i>and brimstone speech.</i>

48:56.634 --> 48:58.601
<i>It looked like</i>
<i>to be more than...</i>

48:58.603 --> 48:59.402
Woman:  <i>You needn't worry.</i>

48:59.404 --> 49:03.039
<i>It isn't you</i>
<i>I intend to hurt,</i>
<i>it's your brother carl.</i>

49:03.041 --> 49:05.374
<i>So don't worry, then.</i>

49:05.376 --> 49:07.476
You seem to like
television stories better.

49:07.478 --> 49:10.346
I mean, compared
to the radio stories.

49:10.348 --> 49:12.548
We do love tv.

49:12.550 --> 49:14.517
At night, my brothers
watch westerns.

49:14.519 --> 49:16.852
Mmm.
<i>Wagon train,</i>
<i>bat masterson.</i>

49:16.854 --> 49:19.488
But come 1:00,
it's  <i>love of life.</i>

49:19.490 --> 49:23.326
(chuckles) I don't care
what type of fit they throw.

49:23.328 --> 49:26.562
Of course,
I work here at 1:00, so...

49:26.564 --> 49:30.099
I appreciate you
turning it on for me.

49:30.968 --> 49:32.568
In the summertime
when the boys are home,

49:32.570 --> 49:35.604
I "ax" my auntie
if I can watch it
at her place.

49:35.606 --> 49:39.642
Mainly so they
don't interrupt me with
all their roughhousing.

49:39.644 --> 49:41.877
"ask."
ma'am?

49:43.213 --> 49:45.414
"ask." uh, you said "ax."

49:45.416 --> 49:48.651
The proper pronunciation
is "ask."

49:49.519 --> 49:52.154
Oh. Yes, ma'am. I'm sorry.

49:52.156 --> 49:53.823
Oh, you don't
have to apologize.

49:53.825 --> 49:55.458
I'm always grateful
when someone points out

49:55.460 --> 49:58.461
Something I could
do better.

49:58.729 --> 50:00.830
Give it a go.

50:02.265 --> 50:03.199
Go?

50:03.201 --> 50:06.435
The pronunciation, "ask."

50:09.006 --> 50:10.506
Ax.

50:11.308 --> 50:13.042
No.

50:13.044 --> 50:15.511
Uh, "ask."

50:18.548 --> 50:20.349
"ask."

50:21.151 --> 50:21.717
In the future,

50:21.719 --> 50:24.954
It would get confusing
if the baby's talking
one way with you

50:24.956 --> 50:26.022
And another with me.

50:26.024 --> 50:28.557
Since we'll be the two
essentially raising him,

50:28.559 --> 50:32.595
It seems a good
idea the two of us
operate as a team.

50:32.597 --> 50:34.897
Don't you think?

50:36.700 --> 50:38.768
Yes, ma'am.

50:48.712 --> 50:51.313
I am so sorry, lillian.

50:56.453 --> 50:58.788
Metastasis was
always a possibility.

50:58.790 --> 51:01.190
But surely
there are options.

51:01.192 --> 51:02.992
What are our options?

51:03.193 --> 51:04.427
It's a good question.

51:04.429 --> 51:07.096
Lillian, you should
probably get dressed.

51:07.098 --> 51:08.631
We can meet in my office,

51:08.633 --> 51:11.000
Go over what's possible
and what's not.

51:11.002 --> 51:14.170
I don't want anyone
to know about this.

51:16.373 --> 51:19.241
Of course.
I won't say anything.

51:26.183 --> 51:27.083
I'll give you your privacy.

51:27.085 --> 51:30.519
A little late for that,
don't you think?

51:32.622 --> 51:33.622
Virginia.

51:33.624 --> 51:35.958
What good did this do?

51:38.728 --> 51:39.829
I...

51:39.831 --> 51:41.530
I know what
to research now.

51:41.532 --> 51:44.967
You're going to
research my metastasized,
terminal cancer?

51:44.969 --> 51:47.570
Is that so
hard to believe?

51:50.340 --> 51:52.108
Then you don't know me.

51:52.110 --> 51:53.042
But I know you.

51:53.044 --> 51:56.045
And you are
a fighter, lillian.
So am I.

51:56.047 --> 51:58.481
And so that is what
we are going to do.

51:58.483 --> 51:59.915
We are going to fight.

51:59.917 --> 52:04.253
Well, every good
fight begins with pizza.

52:05.689 --> 52:07.790
You said "pizza."

52:07.792 --> 52:10.025
What did you mean to say?

52:10.027 --> 52:10.860
Pizza.

52:10.862 --> 52:11.760
After we talk to dr. Lyons,

52:11.762 --> 52:14.964
Is there someplace close to
here that serves pizza?

52:16.133 --> 52:19.101
Gaetano's,
a couple blocks away.

52:19.103 --> 52:21.237
I don't eat pizza.
I don't even like it.

52:21.239 --> 52:24.106
But suddenly
I'm craving pizza.

52:29.880 --> 52:34.783
Woman:  <i>Technician marshall,</i>
<i>please report to x-ray.</i>

52:39.723 --> 52:41.457
Rose palmateer?

52:41.459 --> 52:44.693
For me?
Who are they from?

52:44.695 --> 52:46.695
Oh, uh, no card.

52:46.697 --> 52:48.998
Probably a secret admirer.

52:49.000 --> 52:51.033
Well...

52:51.468 --> 52:53.302
Thank you.

52:53.304 --> 52:55.871
Oh, I didn't catch...
Oh, I'm betty.

52:55.873 --> 52:59.842
Yeah, just one of
the hospital busy bees.

52:59.844 --> 53:02.878
I also work
with doc masters.

53:02.880 --> 53:04.346
Oh. He's my doctor.

53:04.348 --> 53:06.715
Oh, is that so?

53:06.717 --> 53:08.551
So...
So you're leaving, then?

53:08.553 --> 53:11.453
Yeah, my mom's
gonna come pick me up.

53:16.493 --> 53:20.362
It's... It's funny
with mothers, isn't it?

53:20.364 --> 53:22.264
One of my earliest
memories of hospitals,

53:22.266 --> 53:24.633
Uh, my mother
had to go to one.

53:24.635 --> 53:29.805
She had an accident, uh,
ended up blind in one eye.

53:29.807 --> 53:31.340
And it had to be removed.

53:31.342 --> 53:35.578
Um, she had a glass eye
till the day she died.

53:35.580 --> 53:38.047
I'm sorry to hear that.

53:38.782 --> 53:40.616
Actually,
I did it to her.

53:40.618 --> 53:47.323
See, my mother
had a habit of making
me feel real lousy.

53:47.325 --> 53:48.524
She would call me a tramp,

53:48.526 --> 53:53.262
She would say
I was a disgrace
to her and myself.

53:53.264 --> 53:58.400
And I took it
for the longest time,

53:58.402 --> 53:59.101
Her opinion of me,

53:59.103 --> 54:03.606
Until one day,
I don't even know
what set it off,

54:03.608 --> 54:06.141
But I took off
one of my pumps...

54:06.143 --> 54:08.310
It had one of those
real pointy heels,

54:08.312 --> 54:12.848
And I stabbed her
right in the eye with it.

54:13.750 --> 54:18.120
Not that blinding people
is the best way,

54:18.122 --> 54:19.655
Uh, but... (sighs)

54:19.657 --> 54:23.692
There's a life lesson
in there somewhere

54:23.694 --> 54:26.795
About standing up
for yourself.

54:26.797 --> 54:31.500
A life lesson
I am happy to pass on.

54:31.502 --> 54:34.803
You talked to
dr. Masters about me?

54:34.805 --> 54:37.539
Oh, he didn't
say a thing.

54:37.541 --> 54:39.541
I swear. I snooped.

54:39.543 --> 54:41.543
I feel better now anyway.

54:41.545 --> 54:44.713
I'm very grateful
for what he said.

54:44.715 --> 54:45.547
He said something useful?

54:45.549 --> 54:50.653
(chuckles)
he said that I'm just
somebody who needs help,

54:50.655 --> 54:52.021
Like all of us.

54:52.023 --> 54:54.089
And then he said,

54:54.091 --> 54:57.026
"I'll tell you
what you're not, rose.

54:57.028 --> 55:00.095
"you're not
your worst part."

55:01.598 --> 55:05.034
(voice breaking)
I'm not my worst part.

55:07.370 --> 55:08.437
In the morning.

55:08.439 --> 55:11.106
The case just
came in, so I...

55:11.108 --> 55:12.875
Fairly late I'm afraid.

55:12.877 --> 55:15.377
Libby:  <i>I can keep</i>
<i>your dinner warm.</i>

55:15.379 --> 55:18.814
No, lib. Don't wait.
Don't wait. Uh...

55:18.816 --> 55:20.015
I'll eat here.

55:20.017 --> 55:21.617
You should
get some sleep.

55:21.619 --> 55:26.088
<i>True. I am so beat.</i>
<i>In the morning, then?</i>

55:26.090 --> 55:28.290
In the morning.

55:39.536 --> 55:40.602
It might be late.

55:40.604 --> 55:42.705
This day has been,
well, a crazy one,

55:42.707 --> 55:45.240
And if I don't finish
my paperwork...

55:45.242 --> 55:46.108
Don't worry, virginia.

55:46.110 --> 55:47.943
The kids are already down.
I can sit here.

55:47.945 --> 55:49.411
I have loads of
homework to finish.

55:49.413 --> 55:51.080
(sighs) well,
I appreciate it, pam.

55:51.082 --> 55:55.050
You do what
you need to do.
Everything here will be fine.

56:11.735 --> 56:13.902
(engine shuts off)
